GeneralExplanation.Explanation: THE SECRETARY AND CFO REVIEW THE FORM 990 BEFORE FILING IT.

GeneralExplanation.Identifier: Form 990, Part VI, Section B, line 12c
GeneralExplanation.Explanation: THE POLICY IS REVIEWED AND APPROVED ANNUALLY BY THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS. EACH DIRECTOR AND OFFICER IS PROVIDED WITH A COPY OF THE POLICY AT THE ORGANIZATION'S ANNUAL MEETING AND IS REQUIRED TO COMPLETE AND SUBMIT A DISCLOSURE FORM. THE DISCLOSURE FORM REQUIRES THE INTERESTED PERSON TO IDENTIFY ANY RELATIONSHIPS, TRANSACTIONS, POSITIONS HELD (VOLUNTEER OR OTHERWISE), OR CIRCUMSTANCES THAT COULD CONTRIBUTE TO A CONFLICT OF INTEREST BETWEEN THE ORGANIZATION AND THE INTERESTED PERSON'S PERSONAL INTERESTS, FINANCIAL OR OTHERWISE. THE DISCLOSURE FORM ALSO INCLUDES AN ACKNOWLEDGEMENT OF AND AN AGREEMENT TO ABIDE BY THE POLICY.

GeneralExplanation.Identifier: Form 990, Part VI, Section B, line 15a
GeneralExplanation.Explanation: COMPENSATION OF THE ORGANIZATION'S SECRETARY (CEO) IS DETERMINED AND APPROVED BY THE EXECUTIVE COMMITTEE OF THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS, WHICH POSSESSES ALL THE POWERS OF THE FULL BOARD.
